                         *SEARCHING & FILTERS*

_________________________________________________________________________________
grep + "name" + file -- global regular expression print,looks inside files
                        Goal                            Command
                        Simple searchgrep               "text" file.txtSearch
                        case-insensitivegrep -i         "text" file.txt
                        Search entire foldergrep -r     "text" folder/
                        Count occurrencesgrep -c        "text" file.txt
..................................................................................
sort + filename -- sorts files as specified
                   Goal                     Command
                   Alphabetical             sort file.txt
                   Numeric (1, 2, 10)       sort -n file.txt
                   Reverse Order            sort -r file.txt
                   Remove Duplicates        sort -u file.txt
...................................................................................
uniq -- Unique, removes duplicates. always used with sort
        Goal                        Command
        Remove duplicates           sort file.txt | uniq
        Count occurrences           sort file.txt | uniq -c
        Show only repeated lines    sort file.txt | uniq -d
...................................................................................
cut -- helps to narrow down files pretty useful in excel
       Goal                Flag Example
       Set Separator    -d    -d ',' (for comma)
       Select Column    -f    -f 1 (first column)
       Range of Columns    -f    -f 1-3 (columns 1 through 3)
       Characters        -c    -c 1-10 (first 10 letters)
..................................................................................
awk '{ action }' filename -- its a programing language of its own. advanced cut
its like the                 Goal               Command
king of                      Print 1st Column   awk '{print $1}' file
colums                       Print 1st & 3rd    awk '{print $1, $3}' file
                             Add a label        awk '{print "User: " $1}' file
                             Search & Print     awk '/error/ {print $3}' log
...................................................................................
sed -- its a text editor works by comands
       Goal                          Command
       Replace first match          sed 's/old/new/' file
       Replace ALL matches          sed 's/old/new/g' file
       Delete empty lines           sed '/^$/d' file
       Case-insensitive search      sed 's/old/new/Ig' file
