                                *Networks*
____________________________________________________________________________________
ip a -- Show IP Address.

        Goal: Find your local IP (like 192.168...) to test your website on your phone.
....................................................................................
ss -tulpn -- "Socket Statistics." See which apps are using which ports.

Goal: Use this when you get the "Port 3000 already in use" error in React.
....................................................................................
ping -- Check if a website or server is "alive."

        Example: ping google.com (If you get a reply, your internet is working).
....................................................................................
curl -- The Command Line Browser. Downloads or views web content.

        Example: curl http://localhost:3000 (Check if your site is running).
....................................................................................
wget -- "Web Get," used to download files directly from a URL.

Example: wget https://nodejs.org/dist/latest.tar.gz
....................................................................................
netstat (legacy) -- The "Old School" version of ss.

        Note: It's "Legacy," meaning most modern systems prefer you use ss now.
